.........................OSI MODEL........................


the osi model is a 7- layer framework that explains how data from one device to another over a network each layer has a specific role and
communications with the layer directily above and below it 



here's a simple explanation of each layer, starting from the top:

| Layer | Name         | Main Function                                                         | Example                                   |
| ----- | ------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| **7** | Application  | Provides network services to user applications                        | Web browser, email client                 |
| **6** | Presentation | Translates, encrypts, and compresses data                             | SSL/TLS encryption, JPEG, MP3             |
| **5** | Session      | Establishes, manages, and terminates communication sessions           | Login sessions, video calls               |
| **4** | Transport    | Ensures reliable data delivery, error checking, and flow control      | TCP, UDP                                  |
| **3** | Network      | Determines the best path for data and handles logical addressing      | IP, routers                               |
| **2** | Data Link    | Transfers data between devices on the same network and detects errors | Ethernet, MAC addresses, switches         |
| **1** | Physical     | Transmits raw bits over the physical medium                           | Cables, fiber optics, Wi-Fi radio signals |



