##### Layer 6 Presentation ######





•••••presentation..


The Presentation Layer (Layer 6) is responsible for translating, encrypting/decrypting, and compressing data. It ensures that data sent by one device can be understood by another, even if they use different data formats.
Think of it as a translator between the Application Layer and the lower network layers.


Main Functions
1. Data Translation
Different systems may represent data differently. The Presentation Layer converts data into a common format.
Example:
Windows sends text in one encoding.
Linux or macOS receives it.
The Presentation Layer ensures the text is displayed correctly.
2. Encryption
It encrypts data before transmission so that unauthorized people cannot read it.
Example: When you log in to your bank's website using HTTPS, your password is encrypted before being sent.
Common technologies:
SSL
TLS